        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-30 16:56:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI realized that I missed something obvious with this issue in that it's happened on every IB test. I went back and found a spot where I had hardcoded the '@tcp' lnet type. I'll upload a new patch with nettype=o2ib.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7337de706fec175dfe390a5a38993878b2cb17eb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-30 16:57:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThat is to say, the patch will use $NETTYPE and have a Test-Parameters: nettype=o2ib in the commit message.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
